AgriChain Nigeria Roadmap

Phase 1: Research & Planning (Weeks 1–2)

- Research agricultural financing challenges in Nigeria
- Identify key farmer pain points
- Define core platform features
- Create project documentation
- Design user journey and system architecture

Deliverables

- Research report
- Product requirements document
- System design diagram

---

Phase 2: Prototype Design (Weeks 3–4)

- Create UI/UX mockups
- Design farmer dashboard
- Design farm records interface
- Design funding interface
- Gather community feedback

Deliverables

- Complete UI mockups
- User flow diagrams

---

Phase 3: MVP Development (Weeks 5–8)

- Build farmer registration system
- Build farm activity recording module
- Integrate Solana wallet connection
- Build community funding module
- Deploy prototype on Solana Devnet

Deliverables

- Functional MVP
- GitHub repository
- Technical documentation

---

Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Weeks 9–10)

- Conduct user testing
- Fix bugs and improve usability
- Collect feedback from farmers and community members

Deliverables

- Testing report
- Updated MVP

---

Phase 5: Public Launch & Community Engagement (Weeks 11–12)

- Publish open-source code
- Release demo video
- Share project with the Solana community
- Present findings and future plans

Deliverables

- Demo video
- Public GitHub repository
- Final project report
- Community presentation
